This paper deals with optimization problems and the use of evolutionary algorithms to solve them. Specifically, it focuses on niching methods, which are used to identify multiple optima in multimodal domains. This topic is closely related to the field of neural networks (cs.NE), as evolutionary algorithms are often used to train neural networks. Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of algorithms (cs.DS) and the use of probability and statistics (cs.DM) to understand their behavior. The paper also includes experimental studies (cs.AI, cs.LG) to validate the theoretical results.
